      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'll look at those.\n\nactually i was thinking about the \"chaos\" one. usually when these kinds of marches happen and things get a bit messy like the broken windows i mentioned, the media tends to pivot toward describing it as a riot or urban unrest. do you think that's a more \"accurate\" way to frame it for a general audience? like, does the volatility of these specific types of civil rights protests make \"riot\" a more appropriate descriptor than \"march\"?",
